text: Fălticeni (; ; ) is a city in Suceava County, Romania, capital of the former Baia County (1929-1950). As of 2003 the population is 28,899, and the city covers an area of 28,76 km², of which 25% are orchards and lakes. The city is away from Suceava, the capital of the county. ==References== Category:Municipalities of Romania Category:Cities in Suceava County
title: Fălticeni
